snippet.title: Ryan Scott Anderson DENIES Threatening or Controlling Gypsy Rose Blanchard (Exclusive)
snippet.description: “Extra’s” Melvin Robert sits down with Gypsy Rose Blanchard’s estranged husband Ryan Scott Anderson to talk about their split, which viewers will see play out on “Gypsy Rose Blanchard: Life After Lockup.” Ryan reveals that he hasn’t seen Gypsy since they had “a disagreement” and she left, though they have communicated. He says he is “in shellshock mode” over how fast things happened with their divorce and her rekindling with ex Ken Urker. Ryan also denies that he was ever physically threatening to Gypsy or that he controlled her, a suggestion he calls “ludicrous.” Plus, Ryan says his love for Gypsy hasn’t changed — would he want to try to make things work again? “Gypsy Rose Blanchard: Life After Lockup” airs Mondays on Lifetime.

snippet.title: Gypsy Rose Blanchard Shares SURPRISING Updates on Ken, Ryan and Finding a '9 to 5' Job
snippet.description: Gypsy Rose Blanchard shares updates on her romance with Ken Urker, divorce from Ryan Anderson, meeting with Kim Kardashian and plans to get a '9 to 5' job. Gypsy tells ET's Deidre Behar all about rekindling the flame with Ken, whom she was previously engaged to, and shares why they won't live together when he moves to Gypsy's home state of Louisiana. She also opens up about calling off her marriage to Ryan, explaining why and how she knew it was over. After recently meeting Kim Kardashian, Gypsy explains what they discussed and how grateful she is that Kim listened to her thoughts on prison reform. After Gypsy's latest docuseries, 'Gypsy Rose: Life After Lock Up,' premieres on June 3 on Lifetime, she says she plans to return to normal life. Gypsy even reveals the '9 to 5' jobs she's interested in, within the food and beauty industries.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: The YouTuber Who Plotted Her Husband’s Kidnapping and Murder | Prime Crime
snippet.description:
In 2015, authorities were called to a residence in Texas following a distressing claim made by a woman. She alleged that three men had forcibly entered her home, restrained her, and subjected her husband to an attack. Samantha Wohlford, a mother of five and a YouTuber, recounted the chilling events, revealing that the suspects had abducted Ernie Ibarra. Tragically, Ibarra was discovered lifeless in a remote area just one day later. As investigators delved into Wohlford's narrative, inconsistencies began to emerge, prompting a thorough interrogation. Explore the unraveling of Samantha Wohlford narrative in this compelling episode of "Prime Crime with Jesse Weber."

Subscribe for more Law&Crime: https://bit.ly/LawAndCrimeNetwork

The plot thickens as investigators carefully questioned Wohlford, a YouTuber, unraveling the threads of her story. snippet.title: A Snake in Sheep's Clothing — The Disturbing Death of Ben Renick | Prime Crime
snippet.description:
Ben Renick, a famous exotic snake breeder from Missouri, was found dead in a brutal murder scene at his reptile farm in June 2017. His body lay face down in a pool of blood, surrounded by some of the very animals he cared for. Ben's wife and brother initially believed the horrible puncture wounds and crushed skull indicated he was attacked by one of his own snakes. But as investigators arrived at the grisly scene, doubts began creeping in about this first theory.

Subscribe for more Law&Crime: https://bit.ly/LawAndCrimeNetwork

This episode of "Prime Crime with Jesse Weber" unravels what really happened to the beloved local "snake king." As the evidence spirals out like hissing serpents, more sinister motives and suspects emerge in Ben Renick's mysterious death. Finally, a complex murder-for-hire plot reveals a deeply personal betrayal and an intricate coverup at work. Weber analyses what financial elements and disturbed relationships may have led those closest to Renick to want him dead.

snippet.title: Prime Crime: The Chef Killed in His Own Kitchen
snippet.description:
Daniel Brophy was an extraordinary chef who dedicated his life to his craft, teaching at a culinary school in a tranquil suburb of Portland, Oregon. His passion for cooking extended beyond the classroom, as he raised chickens and turkeys in his backyard and grew his own vegetables to create unique, gourmet dishes. Brophy's love for food and his commitment to sharing his knowledge with others made him a beloved figure in the community.

Subscribe for more Law&Crime: https://bit.ly/LawAndCrimeNetwork

Tragically, on June 2, 2018, Daniel Brophy's life was cut short when he was brutally gunned down in the kitchen of the Oregon Culinary Institute, one of the places where he felt most at home. The shocking murder left the culinary world and the Portland community reeling, as they struggled to come to terms with the loss of such a talented and beloved chef. As the investigation into Brophy's death unfolded, suspicion fell on his wife, romance novelist Nancy Crampton Brophy, who had written an essay titled "How to Murder Your Husband" years earlier. Despite her claims of innocence, evidence mounted against her, including surveillance footage, gun purchases, and inconsistencies in her alibi. In May 2022, nearly four years after Daniel Brophy's murder, Nancy Crampton Brophy was found guilty of second-degree murder and unlawful use of a weapon, bringing a measure of justice to the chef's family and friends. This episode of "Prime Crime with Jesse Weber" delves into the shocking details of the case, exploring the events leading up to Daniel Brophy's untimely death and the investigation that ultimately brought his killer to justice.

snippet.title: Srebrenica Genocide Day Marked Globally, but Still a Divisive Issue for Bosnia
snippet.description:
This week marks 29 years since the Bosnian Serb army butchered and killed more than 8,000 Muslim men and boys in and around the town of Srebrenica during the war in Bosnia and Herzegovina. The remains of their bodies have been found in dozens of mass graves in hilly and forested areas in the country's east. The killings happened even as Srebrenica was deemed a safe zone under the protection of the United Nations. This year's anniversary comes just months after the UN General Assembly declared the 11th of July an annual day of remembrance of the genocide. Every year, new victims are identified and given a proper burial.

Across The Balkans, hosted by Nafisa Latic, is TRT World’s programme that focuses specifically on the issues and fault lines shaping Southeast Europe today.

snippet.title: Srebrenica Genocide: No Room For Denial
snippet.description:
In July 1995, forces of the Army of the Republika Srpska, the VRS, invaded the town of Srebrenica, in eastern Bosnia and Herzegovina.

In a few horrific days, more than 8,000 Bosnian Muslim boys and men were taken to places of detention, abused, tortured and then executed.

As their bodies fell into mass graves, the machinery of denial of those crimes was set into motion.

The International Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia-commonly referred to as the ICTY, investigated, prosecuted and passed judgement on those crimes.

This film tells that story. 

Running time: 64 minutes

snippet.title: Srebrenica massacre: A survivor’s fight for justice – BBC Newsnight
snippet.description:
* This film includes graphic scenes which some viewers may find distressing *

Subscribe to our channel here: https://goo.gl/31Q53F 

This is the powerful story of one of the few survivors of the Srebrenica massacre - Europe's worst atrocity since World War Two. 

Nedzad Avdic has returned to Srebrenica and continues to fight for justice. 

Katie Razzall and Maria Polachowska report on his battle to take on those who say genocide never happened.

snippet.title: A Survivor of the War in Bosnia Recounts His Experience | FRONTLINE
snippet.description:
Elvedin Pasic was 14 years old when his village was attacked by Bosnian Serb forces. His emotional story about the last time he saw his father was the first testimony in the trial of General Ratko Mladić — whose forces carried out the genocide of 7,000 Muslim men and boys in Srebrenica, among other crimes.
 
Subscribe on YouTube: http://bit.ly/1BycsJW 

In this scene from "The Trial of Ratko Mladić," the prosecution team prepares Pasic for trial and discusses his importance as a witness. His story “really demonstrates the way Mladić approached war and his willingness to commit terrible crimes,” said lead prosecutor Dermot Groome.
 
Watch "The Trial of Ratko Mladić" online: https://to.pbs.org/2FnU6Vi 
Twitter: https://twitter.com/frontlinepbs 
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/frontline 
Google+: https://plus.google.com/+frontline/posts

snippet.title: How I Survived Being Tortured At 13 | Minutes With | @LADbible TV
snippet.description:
EDIT: It has been brought to our attention that LADbible’s summary of the beginning of the Bosnian conflict could be viewed as an over-simpflication of what was a very complex situation. This was not our intention and we hope it will not take away from the human message, which was the intended focus of the piece.

For a more rounded view on the events from the point of view of lived experience, we recommend reading Mirsad’s book THE BOY WHO SAID NOTHING, available here (global Amazon link): https://relinks.me/B07F99GGW9

To follow Mirsad’s ongoing journey, see his Instagram: @mickey_solak


In this weeks episode of Minutes With we sat down with Mirsad Solakovic, a Bosnian refugee who was forced to flee to the UK with his family. 

Mirsad tells us about the torture he suffered at the hands of his Serbian school teacher, the time he spent in a concentration camp and how this gave him PTSD.

snippet.title: Inside North Korea: Mass Games & Defector Reality Stars | Unreported World | Free Documentary
snippet.description:
Inside North Korea: Mass Games & Defector Reality Stars | Unreported World | Free Documentary

Unreported World - Italy's Mafia Hunters: https://youtu.be/GcS5rih3xIs

00:00:00 North Korea's Greatest Show
Is North Korea changing? Its relations with the rest of the world appear to be thawing after last year’s ‘rocket man’ nuclear missile crisis but does this mean anything is actually changing inside this hermit kingdom? Unreported World joined a business trip aimed at attracting foreign investment just as the country prepared to celebrate its 70th anniversary. Included in Marcel Theroux’s tour is a visit to what North Korea has described as its ‘Benidorm’, the Wonson beach resort, and the country’s only ski resort. But his highlight is a seat at the first Mass Games, the largest choreographed gymnastics event in the world in the world’s biggest stadium, taking place for the first time in five years. The theme of the Games is peace but did he believe the country is really opening up?

00:24:06 North Korea's Reality Stars
Unreported World explores the new genre of primetime TV shows gripping South Korea: 'Defector TV'. For more than half a century North Korea has remained the most closed-off, repressive regime on the planet, fuelling fear and propaganda in South Korea. Now, some of the 30,000 North Korean defectors are finding fame and celebrity on ‘Defector TV' shows and social media by revealing the truth about life under the Kim dynasty. Other defectors-cum-activists are funnelling information in and out across the border in an attempt to undermine Kim Jong-un’s grip on power. Seyi Rhodes investigates what is being coined ‘The Information War’. At every turn this film will reflect what's really happening inside the secret state of North Korea.

snippet.title: Is escaping North Korea really worth it? | Foreign Correspondent
snippet.description:
They’re the refugees from North Korea’s hermit kingdom who overcome huge odds to escape to a new life in South Korea. Most of them are women and the journey they undertake is a perilous one. 

Many are influenced to leave after viewing smuggled South Korean TV dramas which showcase a life of freedom and opportunity. But the reality is often very different. Instead of finding happiness they are overcome with loneliness and isolation.  

On arrival, often after harrowing experiences at the hands of human traffickers, they are placed in a training school and taught how to live in the modern world, South Korean style.

Once on the outside, their accent, clothing and behaviour often make them stand out, and they struggle to assimilate, some often barely surviving. 
Those who do escape are known as defectors and they rarely speak out publicly. 

This week on Foreign Correspondent reporter Naomi Selvaratnam meets some of the North Korean women who are trying to make new lives for themselves in South Korea and asks them: Has their escape been worth it?

snippet.title: Investigating South Korea's Fake Orphans and Sham Adoptions | Foreign Correspondent
snippet.description:
In the decades since the Korean war ended, 200,000 children have been adopted to families worldwide. Now as adults many adoptees are coming back, desperate for information about their birth parents and the circumstances of their adoptions. 

This week on Foreign Correspondent reporter Mazoe Ford investigates the South Korean adoption system. Amidst claims of falsified documents, duplicate identities and even children stolen, she meets the adoptees on a mission to find the truth of the past.

For many, information from the adoption agencies who capitalised on what quickly became a lucrative business has been hard to obtain. Concerns over corruption, malpractice and human rights violations have resulted in an official investigation into Korea’s international adoption scandal.

snippet.title: Living Lonely and Loveless in Japan | Foreign Correspondent
snippet.description:
Around the world more and more people are opting for the single life but in Japan, loneliness has become an epidemic.   Subscribe: https://ab.co/3yqPOZ5
Marriage and childbirth rates are falling, as more and more young Japanese choose to stay single and childless. Relationships are too difficult, they say.

In the country’s last Fertility Survey, figures showed that a quarter of women in their 30s were single, and half of those weren’t interested in having a relationship. 

Many Japanese adults aren’t even having sex. It’s estimated around 10% of people in their 30s are still virgins.
 
By 2040, it’s estimated nearly half of Japan’s population will be single.
Correspondent Jake Sturmer has reported from the ABC’s Tokyo bureau for 4 years and nothing has confounded him more than this social crisis.
As he prepares to return to Australia, Jake sets out on a final journey to discover the forces driving this ‘Solo Society’.

He meets 29-year-old Sayaka, who works in the fashion industry. Sayaka is happily single, and not interested in getting married. 

“I’m under a lot of (social) pressure but I don’t mind,” she says. “There's nothing I can’t do without a man at the moment.”

Instead, the objects of her affection are her dogs - Kogemaru, Unimaru, Rinmaru and Riko - whom she loves to spoil.

Naoya, a 32-year-old creative director for an advertising company, isn’t in a rush to get married either. He often feels lonely but hanging out with friends cheers him up.

“It’s fun drinking with my friends like this and I’m able to fill in the loneliness,” Naoya tells Jake in a cosy bar in downtown Tokyo.

Jake also explores a darker side of Japanese society, meeting a man who has opted out in an extreme way, hiding in his bedroom and avoiding society altogether. He’s what’s called a hikikomori, someone who withdrawn socially. 

In Japan there are more than a million hikikomori. Jake meets the mother of one who’s become an activist, campaigning for Japanese society to be more tolerant of those who don’t fit the mould.

“People believe they need to change the people who’ve withdrawn but I think it’s exactly the opposite. I think the society should change,” she says.

Jake spends time with Masatomi, a cleaner whose job is to clear out the homes of those who die alone. Each year, tens of thousands of Japanese end their lives alone, their bodies often found after neighbours detect an odour. Masatomi is calling for Japanese people to sit up and take notice.

“It’s something that could happen to anybody including myself. I strongly feel that we need to have connections with other people. I feel outrage, why don’t they see what’s going on?"

snippet.title: The North Korea Paradox
snippet.description:
72 Hours Exploring  "The Scariest Place on Earth"
Click my trainwell (formerly CoPilot) link https://go.trainwell.net/JohnnyHarris-cp to get 14 days FREE with your own expert personal trainer!
Go watch a few more subscriber-favorite videos from the channel: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9XECUXXbjhU&list=PLphcdvnT8lOuZ1bOrb33GVM1GwG0cjpnB&index=1

Check out the sources for this video here: https://bit.ly/3D5tVAE

The Border of North and South Korea can seem like a scary place. And yet, in the US we tend to think of everything wrong. In this piece, I jump into an alternative approach to the modern history of this conflict and try to understand why South Koreans aren’t nearly as afraid of North Korea as Americans are.

snippet.title: Why the US Military is Preparing for War With China
snippet.description:
How the US is Militarizing the Pacific
Click my trainwell (formerly CoPilot) link https://go.trainwell.net/JohnnyHarris-cp to get 14 days FREE with your own expert personal trainer!

snippet.title: What happens if China invades Taiwan?
snippet.description:
The next invasion?
Get an exclusive deal from NordVPN by clicking this link: https://nordvpn.com/johnnyharris

We publish an extra video every month over at https://www.patreon.com/johnnyharris

What happens if China invades Taiwan? Here’s how the start of World War 3 might go down.

For this video I leaned on some excellent interviews and research form:
Oriana Skylar Mastro: https://fsi.stanford.edu/people/oriana-skylar-mastro
Michael O’Hanlon: https://www.brookings.edu/experts/michael-e-ohanlon/

Also, Reuters did a similar speculative piece using some really compelling visuals: https://www.reuters.com/investigates/special-report/taiwan-china-wargames/

Ian Easton’s research using PLA internal documents was a strong foundation for my reporting on this: https://project2049.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Chinas-Top-Five-War-Plans_Ian_Easton_Project2049.pdf

Excellent data gathering and analysis by Gerald C. Brown at FPRI: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1qbfYF0VgDBJoFZN5elpZwNTiKZ4nvCUcs5a7oYwm52g/edit?usp=sharing

Putin is taking over land, but losing the war.

snippet.title: 7 Of The Most Faked Seafoods In The World | Big Business | Business Insider
snippet.description:
According to the ocean-conservation nonprofit Oceana, seafood may be one of the most commonly fraudulent foods we come in contact with. Your red snapper could actually be a tilapia fillet. That wild-caught salmon? It could be farm-raised. Crab, lobster, and scallops have also been victims of fraudulent swaps — some of the substitutions could harm human health. But there are also entire criminal rings smuggling seafood across the world. They often fish illegally and have been involved in human trafficking. Why is it so hard to catch bad actors in seafood supply chains? And how can we ensure we're getting the seafood on the label?

snippet.title: Why Single-Origin Coffee Is So Expensive | So Expensive Food | Insider Business
snippet.description:
Single-origin specialty coffee can cost over $30 per pound, more than five times the average price of 1 pound of ground coffee in the US. “Specialty” is the term for the highest-quality coffee, and aficionados describe its taste with words more frequently used by sommeliers, like “floral” or “fruity.” Reaching this level of quality requires investment and labor at every step of production. But despite the prices a roasted bag of single-origin coffee can reach in the world’s wealthiest countries, the farmers who handpick each coffee cherry struggle to earn a profit. 

We went to Kenya to find out what it takes to grow high-quality coffee, and why it’s so expensive.

snippet.title: Are you buying the right Coffee Beans? (Beginner's Guide to Coffee)
snippet.description:
Head to https://www.aeropress.com/ethan and save 20% off your order! A huge thank you to AeroPress for sponsoring this video.

Coffee beans are one of the most confusing items to purchase, so over the past several weeks, I bought 20+ different kinds of coffee at different price points, visited a local roaster, tried roasting my own beans at home and tested a bunch of types of coffee in order to understand the flavor and price differences of coffee beans.

▶️ My second channel ➡ https://www.youtube.com/@Cookwelldotcom
🍔  The Mouthful Sunday Newsletter (free)➡ https://www.ethanchlebowski.com/newsletter

SOURCES:
  📗 The World Atlas of Coffee, James Hoffmann: https://amzn.to/4dSDOlA
  📗 Barista Hustle (Articles, Research, & Courses) - https://www.baristahustle.com/
  📗 Specialty Coffee Association (Flavor Wheel & Cupping Handbook): https://sca.coffee/store-index/coffee-sensory-cupping-handbook
  📗 Modulating the Flavor Profile of Coffee, Rob Hoos: https://www.nossacoffee.com/products/modulating-the-flavor-profile-of-coffee-by-rob-hoos
  📗 Coffee Varieties Manual (World Coffee Research): https://cdn2.assets-servd.host/worldcoffee-research/production/pdf/World-Coffee-Research-Arabica-Varieties.pdf
  📗 Coffee Market Statistics: https://icocoffee.org/resources/coffee-market-report-statistics-section/

snippet.title: Intel's CPUs Are Failing, ft. Wendell of Level1 Techs
snippet.description:
Sponsor: NZXT C1500 Platinum PSU on Amazon https://geni.us/KvKlUi
Intel's CPUs, including the 14900K and 13900K (and others of those generations) have had ramping instability reports from consumers for months now, but Wendell of Level1 Techs has sources stating that Intel's CPUs are also failing in enterprise and server deployments. This concerning development suggests that some of the prior PL1 and PL2 configuration issues may be a different issue or red herring, as the server boards don't push power to the same extent as the consumer Z790 motherboards. We talk with Wendell about what this means and what's next for Intel.

Watch Wendell's video! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QzHcrbT5D_Y

The best way to support our work is through our store: https://store.gamersnexus.net/

Like our content? Please consider becoming our Patron to support us: http://www.patreon.com/gamersnexus

snippet.title: FIRST LOOK: Red Bull RB17 Hypercar – 1200hp, 15,000rpm, Fast As F1!
snippet.description:
This is the Red Bull RB17 – and it’s much more than F1 design genius Adrian Newey’s greatest hits amalgamated into a hypercar.

Sure, this £5m, track-only spaceship has the likes of a blown diffuser and Newey’s favourite Formula 1 engine configuration (a naturally aspirated V10) but the RB17 is instead what happens when Newey isn’t trying to find loopholes in restrictive Formula 1 regulations. The RB17 is what happens when Newey is unleashed!

The result, the mind-blowing result, is a car (very rich) mere mortals can buy – and one that can lap a racetrack as fast as a contemporary Formula 1 car.

Behind Newey is the might of Red Bull Applied Technologies, the sister company to Red Bull Racing that uses the F1 team’s know-how and applies it to wider engineering challenges. As a calling card to show their expertise, the RB17 is quite something.

But enough of us telling you about it. Instead, here’s the man himself, interviewed by Top Gear’s Editor-at-Large, Jason Barlow…

snippet.title: Quickest American Car Ever: Demon 170 vs Lucid Sapphire VHT & Asphalt — Cammisa Ultimate Drag Race
snippet.description:
Let’s settle the debate on regular pavement and VHT: which is the quickest accelerating American car in history, the Dodge Challenger SRT Demom 170 or the Lucid Air Sapphire?

=
This episode is presented by Valentine One Radar Locator: Find radar before it finds you https://bit.ly/Valentine1_Hagerty
Click here to join the Hagerty Driver's Club: https://bit.ly/Join-HDC-Cammisa-UDRR
=

In this episode, we race the two most powerful American production cars in history, the 1234-hp Lucid Air Sapphire and the 1025-hp Dodge Challenger SRT D170.

The first race takes place on regular asphalt, with our standard weather-corrected numbers. With the help of veteran drag racer, we achieve the quickest 0-60 and ¼-mile times ever seen from a Challenger. But is that enough to beat the Sapphire?

Either way, the Demon’s Mickey Thompson drag radials aren’t meant for an unprepped surface, so we leave Willow Springs and head to the Famoso Drag Strip to race on “glue” — the VHT-prepped surface. 

Here, Tom Bailey’s experience launching the Challenger pays dividends as we try to recreate Dodge’s claimed 8.91-second quarter-mile run and dethrone the Lucid. Will it work?

Let’s fight about it.

Chapters:
0:00 America Divided: ICE vs EV
1:16 The Dodge Challenger SRT Demon 170 Specs
2:43 The Lucid Air Sapphire Specs
4:21 Asphalt Race: Demon 170 vs Lucid Sapphire
5:04 Drag Race Replay: What Happened?
8:53 Results and Willow Springs Conclusion
9:27 Moving to Famoso Drag Strip
9:42 What is VHT?
10:29 What is Rollout?
11:07 How do the Timing Lights Work?
12:55 Demon vs Sapphire race on VHT
14:53 Conclusion and Results

===

Performance Testing Results: 

Lucid Air Sapphire
0-60: 2.1 seconds
¼-mile: 9.2 sec @ 158 mph

Dodge Challenger SRT Demon 170
0-60: 3.7 seconds
¼-mile: 11.2 sec @ 139 mph


VHT Prepped Surface Results:
Lucid Air Sapphire: 9.002 sec @ 155.57 mph (0-60 in 1.92 sec)
Dodge SRT Demon 170: 9.721 sec @ 143.72 mph

snippet.title: New RED BULL RB17! Adrian Newey's Track Hypercar is HERE
snippet.description:
This is the brand new RED BULL RB17! Join me at Red Bull HQ in Milton Keynes for a first look at Adrian Newey's new creation, the £5.75M ultimate track hypercar. Limited to 50 cars, featuring an NA V10, and the most incredible aerodynamics, we're taking a full tour in detail. Let's check it out!

Having been involved in the AM-RB 001 project that became the Aston Martin Valkyrie, this time around Adrian Newey has been working on creating a new hypercar under the Red Bull name. Adrian's work goes without introduction as one of the most successful engineers of the Formula 1 world, notably in the recent years with Max Verstappen. However, this time around, it's a road car coming from Red Bull Advanced Technologies.

In 2021, the F1 regulations were on hold, so the RB17 never 'existed', a jump from the RB16 and RB16B to RB18. The space is now filled by a new track hypercar, limited to 50 units, powered by a 4.5l NA V10 that revs to 15,000rpm, in a vehicle that weights sub-900kg and boasts downforce figures almost 2x its weight. We're exploring the new car in detail with Rob Gray, Technical Direction behind the project to understand more of what it's all about and the plans ahead.

It has been an honour to visit Red Bull and explore the new RB17 ahead of the global debut, and to preview it with Rob to share with you.

Thanks for watching, Tim

snippet.title: The GMA T.50s Completes the World's Best Supercar Parking!
snippet.description:
There's nothing quite like the Goodwood Festival of Speed for bringing together all of the latest and greatest supercars! Let's check out the Supercar Paddock with highlights like the GMA T.50s, Aston Martin Valiant, Bugatti Mistral, Pagani Epitome and more!

There's a lot to see and take in when you explore the Supercar Paddock, with amazing displays from the best manufacturers like Ferrari, Lamborghini, Aston Martin and McLaren, plus plenty more. There are cars on the hill including the Ferrari SF90 XX Spider, Ferrari SP-8 Special Project, Bugatti Bolide, McLaren Solus GT, Pagani Huayra R, and more.

With everything in attendance, we can explore the line-up as the cars prepare for the first hillclimb outing. There's a mind blowing display also including the new Bugatti Tourbillon, a squad of different Paganis including 7 Zondas, the MadMike 'P1 GTR', HWA EVO, multiple McLaren F1s, and just so much, it's time to take in the action at the start line!

Lastly, but of course by no means least, upon return to the paddock we can see the cars rolling back into the paddock at the paddock at the Festival of Speed, thank you to everyone involved in it.

Thanks for watching, Tim

There's nothing quite like the Goodwood Festival of Speed for bringing together all of the latest and greatest supercars! Let's check out the Supercar Paddock with highlights like the GMA T.50s, Aston Martin Valiant, Bugatti Mistral, Pagani Epitome and more!

There's a lot to see and take in when you explore the Supercar Paddock, with amazing displays from the best manufacturers like Ferrari, Lamborghini, Aston Martin and McLaren, plus plenty more. There are cars on the hill including the Ferrari SF90 XX Spider, Ferrari SP-8 Special Project, Bugatti Bolide, McLaren Solus GT, Pagani Huayra R, and more.

With everything in attendance, we can explore the line-up as the cars prepare for the first hillclimb outing. There's a mind blowing display also including the new Bugatti Tourbillon, a squad of different Paganis including 7 Zondas, the MadMike 'P1 GTR', HWA EVO, multiple McLaren F1s, and just so much, it's time to take in the action at the start line!

Lastly, but of course by no means least, upon return to the paddock we can see the cars rolling back into the paddock at the paddock at the Festival of Speed, thank you to everyone involved in it.

Thanks for watching, Tim

snippet.title: [English] GT World Series 2024 | Round 1 - Montreal | Nations Cup
snippet.description:
The Nations Cup returns to an individual format for the first live event of 2024 in Montreal, Canada!

Top drivers selected from the six rounds of the Online Qualifiers will compete across three live events before the World Finals of the 2024 Nations Cup series. This year's lineup features veteran drivers from the Gran Turismo World Series, including Spanish drivers Jose Serrano and Coque López who dominated the field last season, along with some hot rookie drivers selected from across the globe for a total of 12 drivers. Who will survive the onslaught of fastest drivers in the world and stand tall upon the podium at this year's first live event in Montreal?

This time sees the introduction of a separate Live Timing stream where viewers can check position changes, sector times, and other race statistics in real time. We hope you enjoy this new feature.
https://youtube.com/live/4lS7t0p7sEY

00:10:36 Countdown

snippet.title: [English] GT World Series 2024 | Round 1 - Montreal | Manufacturers Cup
snippet.description:
The Gran Turismo World Series 2024 Series first live event kicks off in Montreal, Canada!

Official partners Toyota, Genesis, and Mazda face off against the top ranked manufacturer teams from the six rounds of the Online Qualifiers in a 12-team showdown. For the Montreal event, these teams will be represented by drivers from the Americas Region.

With veteran drivers in the hot seat, Lexus, Toyota, and Subaru seek to reclaim the title. Meanwhile Chevrolet and Audi gear up for a triumphant return to live events. Are last year's top manufacturers up for the challenge?

This time sees the introduction of a separate Live Timing stream where viewers can check position changes, sector times, and other race statistics in real time. We hope you enjoy this new feature.
https://youtube.com/live/S2_OjQYraQU

snippet.title: [Deutsch] GT World Series 2024 | Runde 1 - Montreal | Manufacturers Cup
snippet.description:
Das erste Live-Event der Gran Turismo World Series 2024 startet in Montreal!

Die offiziellen Partner Toyota, Genesis und Mazda treten in einem Showdown mit 12 Teams gegen die bestplatzierten Herstellerteams aus den sechs Runden der Online-Qualifyings an. In Montreal werden diese Teams von Fahrern aus der Region Amerika vertreten.

Mit echten Rennveteranen am Steuer wollen Lexus, Toyota und Subaru den Titel zurückerobern. Derweil bereiten sich Chevrolet und Audi auf eine triumphale Rückkehr in die Live-Events vor. Werden die besten Hersteller des letzten Jahres der Herausforderung gewachsen sein?

In diesem Jahr wird ein separater Echtzeit-Stream eingeführt, in dem sich die Zuschauer Positionswechsel, Sektorzeiten und andere Rennstatistiken in Echtzeit ansehen können. Wir hoffen, dass Ihnen diese neue Funktion gefallen wird.
https://youtube.com/live/S2_OjQYraQU

snippet.description:
Subscribe for new videos every week! https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCpYye8D5fFMUPf9nSfgd4bA?sub_confirmation=1

❤ Sheriff Labrador's Safety Talk ❤
Kids, when learning something new, always stay humble and try your best.

snippet.title: Unique Fingerprints | Educational Cartoons for Kids | Sheriff Labrador
snippet.description:
Subscribe for new videos every week! https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCXIvAXVdbUDzIFhVwB9RR-g?sub_confirmation=1

❤ Sheriff Labrador's Safety Talk ❤
Kids, look closely at your fingertips. You'll see lots of tiny lines, which are called fingerprints.Everyone's fingerprints are unique, even twins have different patterns.Fingerprints are used in many ways, like unlocking phones, logging into tablets, and home smart locks. Police also use them to find and catch bad people. Where else are fingerprints used? Keep an eye out for your daily life!

snippet.title: MR MEN & LITTLE MISS - 30 minutes - Compilation #12
snippet.description:
MR MEN & LITTLE MISS - 30minutes - Compilation #12

EP56 - Mr Forgetful, the world best actor! - 00:00 - 05:01

Mr Uppity is looking for an actor for his film. He hires Mr Forgetful who, as it turns out, is totally incapable of memorizing his lines. But the film is rapidly to become a comedy, for Mr Forgetful invents his lines as he goes along. Finally, he is awarded the “Golden Duck award” for the originality of his performance. 

EP57 - Hello, pizza express ? -  06:00 10:59

Mr Busy delivers pizzas. He really has his work cut out, but everything goes according to plan until his scooter breaks down… By good fortune, he catches sight of Little Miss Somersault in her little plane that offers to help him. With Little Miss Somersault’s assistance, now Mr Busy can really provide an express delivery!

EP58 - Mr clumsy, head butler - 12:00 - 16:56

Mr Messy is hired as head butler for Little Miss Star’s party. But she has no idea of what is in store, for Mr Messy, as his name suggests, is not the tidiest of people. Little Miss Splendid leaves in a huff on discovering, to her horror, a family of living snails on her hat. As for Mr Uppity, all that remains of his beautiful white scarf is a rag covered with big black stains! What an evening!

EP59 - Mr Impossible's lesson - 18:00 22:59

Mr Uppity’s house is burning down but what help can he possibly expect from Little Miss Shy, Mr Clumsy and Mr Bump? But he hadn’t banked on the presence of Mr Impossible, who makes himself invisible and changes our three friends into valorous firemen. Thanks to Mr Impossible, all’s well that ends well and Mr Uppity is obliged to thank him for his unexpected assistance. 

EP60 - Little Miss Star goes to Jollywood - 24:00 - 29:02

Little Miss Star dreams that she is a star in Jollywood, but her dream rapidly becomes a nightmare when journalists and photographers bombard her from all sides. She wakes up with a start, relieved to find that it has all been a dream. But her “dream” is soon to become reality for she wins a contest whose first prize is: a day in Jollywood.

snippet.title: MR MEN & LITTLE MISS - 30 minutes - Compilation #13
snippet.description:
MR MEN & LITTLE MISS - 30 minutes - Compilation #13

EP61 - Mr clever's invention - 00:00 - 05:01

The proud inventor of a stance spacecraft, Mr Clever takes on board MR Grumble and Little Miss Giggles for a trip to Mars. After a bumpy landing, our three friends set foot on a wasteland strewn with all kinds of objects, to the great delight for Mr Clever. But what a disappointment when he realizes that he is on a public rubbish dump, only a hundred yards from his own house!

EP62 - Little miss chatterbox finds her calling - 06:00 - 10:59

Mr Happy thinks he has had a good idea in hiring Little Miss Chatterbox as prompter in his theatre. But this isn’t at all to the liking of the actors, who can hardly say a word without Little Miss Chatterbox cutting them off in their prime. Finally, the three actors walk out in a huff and it’s Little Miss Chatterbox who takes over their roles. Ger performance is so spectacular, but such a strain on the vocal chords, that she ends up losing her voice!

EP63 - Mr skinny incredible bet - 12:00 - 16:56

Mr Skinny has laid a bet that he can get fatter than Mr Greedy, but try as he might; he is incapable of eating more. He then has a brainwave and asks Mr Tickle to call on Mr Greedy and tickle him every time he is about to eat. Several days later, Mr Greedy is indeed thinner than Mr Skinny. Mr Skinny has finally won his bet, but not as we might have imagined!

EP64 - Little miss busy, d.i.y. teacher - 18:00 - 22:59

Little Miss Busy gets bored as soon as she has nothing to do. So she decides to found a D.I.Y. school. But trying to teach pupils like Mr Bump, Mr Clumsy, Mr Dizzy, Mr Lazy and Mr Silly how to build a house is by no means an easy task! But not for the radiant Little Miss Busy, who is delighted at having her work cut out with such unpromising pupils!

EP65 - Little miss chatterbox goes to sea-town - 24:00 - 29:02

Little Miss Chatterbox is on holiday at Sea-town. Whilst walking on the beach one day, she meets Mr Grumpy and Little Miss Busy, who are preparing to participate in the big regatta with their sailing boat. Little Miss Chatterbox immediately climbs on board, without giving them time to object. But there isn’t the tiniest puff of wind and Mr Grumpy has given up all hope of winning. That is, until Little Miss busy has the bright idea of encouraging Little Miss Chatterbox to talk and talk, which makes more than enough air to allow our three friends to win the regatta!

snippet.title: MR MEN & LITTLE MISS - 30minutes - Compilation #9
snippet.description:
MR MEN & LITTLE MISS - 30minutes - Compilation #9

EP41 -  Little Miss Star, the leading witness - 00:00 - 05:01

Little Miss Star will do anything to get in the headlines. So she hides in Mr Dizzy’s house, to make people think she has been kidnapped. Everything goes according to plan, for her disappearance is the subject of much concern in the news. 
 The next day, she appears on television, disguised as the Masked Avenger and pretends to be the number 1 witness in the investigation. But her ploy is soon thwarted and Little Miss Star will only have been famous for one day. 
What a stroke of luck! A production from Jollywood has seen Little Miss Star as the Masked Avenger on television and he hires her for his next film!

EP42 - Little Miss Late, beat them all! - 06:00 - 10:59

A race is organized in Misterland and Little Miss Late decides to participate, but without holding out much hope of winning. 
But thanks to Mr Mischief, who sets trap for all the participants, Little Miss Late soon finds herself in second position, right behind Mr Mischief himself. 
As luck would have it, he trips up just before reaching the finishing line, which puts Little Miss Late in first position!

EP43 - Mr Skinny is up the spout - 12:00 - 16:56

Mr Skinny is about to have a bath, as he gets ready to go to the village party. Afterwards, he pulls the plug out and by misfortune, finds himself sucked down the drain along with the water. He ends up in the sewer, where he meets Mr Messy, who advises him to trace one of the countless pipes back to his house. 
But the first one leads to Mr Grumble’s house, the next to Mr Worry’s. And so, he finds himself back in the sewer again… but thanks to Mr Messy, who shows him which pipe leads to the village square, Mr Skinny’s surprise appearance makes him the star of the party!

EP44 - That's gratitude, Mr Uppity! - 18:00 - 22:59

Mr Uppity is always very unpleasant with everyone but, when he finds himself in hospital following a bad fall, his friends Little Miss Splendid, Mr Mischief and Mr Greedy do their utmost to look after him. And to everyone’s great surprise, he says… “Thank you”, for the first time in his life!

EP45 - Little Miss Neat sees spots - 24:00 - 29:02

Little Miss Neat invites Mr Clumsy to lunch but no sooner has he arrived than he trips up and spills the cup of hot chocolate he is carrying. Little Miss Neat spends the whole day scrubbing her flat to get rid of the stains but to no avail; they refuse to budge!
But luckily, Mr Fussy points out that the stains aren’t on the walls but… on her glasses!

snippet.title: MR MEN & LITTLE MISS - 30 minutes - Compilation #10
snippet.description:
MR MEN & LITTLE MISS - 30 minutes - Compilation #10

EP46 - Mr Grumble boils over - 00:00 - 05:01

It is the middle of summer. Misterland is totally deserted, except for Mr Grumble and Mr Worry. But Mr Worry is too worried to stay alone. So he decides to seek comfort with Mr Grumble, which isn’t a good idea at all, since Mr Grumble hates surprise visits. Poor Mr Worry will have a hard time making himself welcome to such a discourteous host!

EP47 - Another victory for Little Miss Splendid - 06:00 - 10:59

Little Miss Splendid is getting ready for the beauty contest! She goes to the hairdresser’s and, thanks to Mr Dizzy’s absentmindedness, ends up as bald as a coot!  
And, as it never rains but it pours, she then falls into a pot of glue before finally ending up in Mr Strong’s lorry, which is transporting chickens. 
Little Miss Splendid finds herself covered with feathers from head to toe, which seems to go down very well with the jury at the beauty contest since she is proclaimed the winner, yet again!

EP48 - A surprise for Mr Tall - 12:00 - 16:56

Poor Mr Tall is very worried indeed for he considers himself too tall and this prevents him from living a normal life. Little Miss Magic soon puts things to rights and Mr Tall finds himself a perfectly normal size. But the only problem is that now, nobody recognises him! What a shame, since the Mr Men have prepares a huge birthday cake for him!
By good fortune, Little Miss Magic is there and Mr Tall becomes the real Mr Tall again that everyone knows and loves. 

EP49 - The joke is on Little Miss Naughty - 18:00 - 22:59

Some of the Mr Men have organised a picnic on the beach, but Little Miss Naughty is prowling around, always ready to play a prank on someone. She decides to put sand in the saltcellar instead of salt… But Little Miss Naughty is mistaken in taking the Mr Men for fools, because they end up inviting her to their picnic and guess what is on the menu? Hard-boiled eggs dipped in “salt”!
Now you are caught at your own act, Little Miss Naughty!

EP50 - Mr Cheerful doffs his hat - 24:00 - 29:02

Mr Cheerful is in the process of teaching three of his friends how to dance and is giving them a demonstration. They are convinced that the hat which he wears all the time is the secret of his cheerfulness. In an attempt to find out the truth of the matter, Mr Tickle lifts Mr Cheerful’s hat off, to find that he only has three hairs on his head! Deprived of his hat, Mr Cheerful is totally lost, but his friends quickly convince him that he is still the same Mr Cheerful, with or without his hat!

snippet.title: MR MEN & LITTLE MISS - 30 minutes - Compilation #11
snippet.description:
MR MEN & LITTLE MISS - 30 minutes - Compilation #11

EP21 - Little Miss Scatterbrain puts everything in turmoil - 00:00 - 05:01

Little Miss Scatterbrain goes shopping for her birthday and then drives back home to get ready for her party. 
All of which is fine, except that it isn’t her birthday, the car is Mr Topsy-Turvy’s and not hers and it isn’t her house to which she returns but Mr Jelly’s! The string of misunderstandings is to be the cause of many a surprise!

EP52 - Mr Clever's daft bet - 06:00 - 10:59

Mr Clever, Mr Jelly and Little Miss Fun are in a mountain chalet. Mr Clever bets that they don’t dare spend a whole night in the tent. Little Miss Fun takes up the bet and talks poor Mr Jelly who is already trembling with fear, into following suit. The newt day, Mr Clever starts to gloat on seeing no tent outside, thinking that he has won his bet. But when he goes downstairs, he finds the tent planted in the middle of the sitting room with our two friends sound asleep inside!

EP53 - What a mess, Little Miss Helpful!  - 12:00 - 16:56

Little Miss Helpful is hired to do the housework at Mr Uppity’s, but as she breaks everything she touches, Little Miss Magic has to step in to set things to rights. 
Amidst the general panic, Little Miss Magic loses her magic wand, which Little Miss Helpful finds and quickly returns to its owner. Everything would have turned out just fine if only Little Miss Helpful hadn’t broken Little Miss Magic’s wand in two!

EP54 - Little Miss Tidy and the winning ticket - 18:00 - 22:59

Little Miss Tidy has won the jackpot! As she’s leaving her house, the lottery ticket is swept out of the window by an unfortunate gust of wind before falling into the hands of Mr Mean who, though very mean, is certainly not dishonest! E runs to give it back to Little Miss Tidy who, as a reward but mainly because she doesn’t know where to put all that money without making a mess… gives him the lottery ticket!

EP55 - Mr Dizzy promises the moon - 24:00 - 29:02

Mr Dizzy has taken it into his head to promise the moon to the little children; but what a difficult promise to keep! Mr Cheerful and Little Miss Greedy are to make his dream come true by making a magnificent moon out of silver cardboard and hanging in the night. Thanks to his two friends, Mr Dizzy has been able to keep his promise to the children.
